minitimer
------------------------------------------
Mini Timer is a very simple timer that lives in the terminal of your system. It
also provides a named pipe which you can pass commands to to control a running
instance of Mini Timer.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.4.5-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.39-1
  cygport-0.36.0-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  make-4.4-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/ariadnavigo/minitimer

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/ariadnavigo/minitimer/archive/refs/tags/4.2.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack minitimer-4.2.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./minitimer-4.2.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/minitimer-4.2.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/minitimer-4.2.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(minitimer)
  /usr/bin/minitimer.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/minitimer.README
  /usr/share/doc/minitimer/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/minitimer/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man1/minitimer.1.gz

